claim.claim-text:
1. A drag reducing device for use in reducing drag on a vehicle, the drag reducing device comprising:
a drag reducing assembly that is movable between a deployed configuration and a stowed configuration, the drag reducing assembly including a mount adapted for connection to the vehicle and a deployed portion that is moved away from the mount when the drag reducing assembly is moved from the stowed configuration toward the deployed configuration;
a drive arrangement; and
a rotary motor for moving the drive arrangement, the drive arrangement adapted to cause the drag reducing assembly to move toward the deployed configuration under power of the rotary motor;
wherein a tensile load is transferred through the drive arrangement to move the drag reducing assembly from the stowed configuration toward the deployed configuration, the tensile load at least partially extending along a rearward direction of the vehicle.

5. A drag reducing device for use in reducing drag on a vehicle, the drag reducing device movable between a deployed configuration and a stowed configuration, the drag reducing device comprising:
a mount adapted for connection to the vehicle;
a deployed portion that is moved away from the mount when the drag reducing device is moved from the stowed configuration toward the deployed configuration; and
a set of linkages that interconnect the mount to the deployed portion, the set of linkages substantially maintaining a parallel orientation between the mount and the deployed portion;
wherein the set of linkages guides the deployed portion along a substantially linear path.

16. A drag reducing device for use in reducing drag on a vehicle, the drag reducing device movable between a deployed configuration and a stowed configuration, the drag reducing device comprising:
a mount adapted for connection to the vehicle;
a deployed portion that is moved away from the mount when the drag reducing device is moved from the stowed configuration toward the deployed configuration; and
a set of linkages that interconnect the mount to the deployed portion, the set of linkages substantially maintaining a parallel orientation between the mount and the deployed portion;
wherein the set of linkages includes a first linkage and a second linkage and wherein a first group of pivoting axes of the first linkage are non-parallel with a second group of pivoting axes of the second linkage.

17. A drag reducing device for use in reducing drag on a vehicle, the drag reducing device movable between a deployed configuration and a stowed configuration, the drag reducing device comprising:
a mount adapted for connection to the vehicle;
a deployed portion including an end that is moved away from the mount when the drag reducing device is moved from the stowed configuration toward the deployed configuration; and
a set of linkages that interconnect the mount to the deployed portion, the set of linkages substantially maintaining an orientation between the vehicle and the end of the deployed portion;
wherein the set of linkages includes a first linkage and a second linkage and wherein a first group of pivoting axes of the first linkage are non-parallel with a second group of pivoting axes of the second linkage.

18. A drag reducing device for use in reducing drag on a vehicle, the drag reducing device movable between a deployed configuration and a stowed configuration, the drag reducing device comprising:
a mount adapted for connection to the vehicle;
a deployed portion including an end that is moved away from the mount when the drag reducing device is moved from the stowed configuration toward the deployed configuration; and
a set of linkages that interconnect the mount to the deployed portion, the set of linkages substantially maintaining an orientation between the vehicle and the end of the deployed portion;
wherein the set of linkages guides the deployed portion along a substantially linear path.
